# Employee Module — Production-Level Self-Service Upgrade

Upgrade the existing Employee module from a basic 5-route dashboard into a full-featured, production-level Employee Self-Service Portal. The employee module will **consume** data from HR and Finance and **follow rules** from Admin — it will **never** implement admin/HR/finance logic itself.

## Existing State

The current Employee module has only 5 routes:
- Dashboard (basic stats)
- Profile (name + phone edit only)
- My Tasks (read-only list)
- My Leaves (list + request form)

## Proposed Changes

### Architecture Overview

```
app/employee/
├── __init__.py          # Blueprint definition (existing, minor update)
├── routes.py            # All route handlers (rewrite — expanded from 5 to ~25 routes)
├── services.py          # [NEW] Business logic layer — self-service operations
├── forms.py             # WTForms (rewrite — expanded from 2 to ~8 forms)
├── schemas.py           # [NEW] Input validation & response formatting utilities
└── utils.py             # [NEW] Helpers (logging, notification creation, etc.)
```

---

### New Database Tables (added to `app/models.py`)

#### 1. `ProfileUpdateRequest` — Employee submits profile changes for HR approval
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| id | Integer PK | Auto |
| employee_id | FK → employees | Who is requesting |
| field_name | String(50) | e.g. "phone", "bank_account" |
| old_value | String(250) | Current value |
| new_value | String(250) | Requested value |
| status | String(20) | Pending / Approved / Rejected |
| reviewed_by | FK → users | HR user who reviewed |
| created_at | DateTime | When submitted |
| reviewed_at | DateTime | When reviewed |

#### 2. `EmployeeExpense` — Employee submits expense/reimbursement claims
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| id | Integer PK | Auto |
| employee_id | FK → employees | Submitter |
| category | String(60) | Travel, Software, Medical, etc. |
| amount | Float | Claim amount |
| date | Date | Expense date |
| description | Text | Details |
| receipt_filename | String(250) | Uploaded receipt file |
| receipt_original | String(250) | Original filename |
| status | String(20) | Pending / Approved / Rejected |
| reviewed_by | FK → users | Finance/HR reviewer |
| created_at | DateTime | Submission time |

> [!NOTE]
> These are **separate** from the existing `Expense` model (which is a Finance-side corporate expense tracker). `EmployeeExpense` is for employee reimbursement claims that flow to Finance for approval.

